const intro = [
  'Cheshire’s housing stock is incredibly varied—from sandstone cottages on the River Dee and grand Victorian terraces in Crewe, to barn conversions, new garden villages and waterside apartments. Each project demands a tailored inspection to understand condition, future maintenance and potential for improvement.',
  'Growth around Chester, Northwich, Winsford and Warrington has brought extensive extensions, loft conversions and retrofit upgrades. We examine how these changes integrate with original structures, the quality of drainage and ventilation, and any paperwork needed to keep transactions moving.',
  'Clients across the county rely on us for clear, independent advice that balances technical detail with realistic budgets. Whether you are buying a listed townhouse, a commuter estate property or a farmhouse ready for renovation, you receive practical reporting and responsive support.',
];

